tables.name: ads_incident_report_data
tables.description:
# ADS Incident Report Data
This repository shows the observations from the reported crashes of automated driving systems (ADS)-equipped vehicles.

## Usage Notes
From the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. If there is confusion in classifying the onboard automation system

>  as ADS is mistakenly classified as Level 2 ADAS (and vice versa), the values from the latest report are used. Only those clearly identified ADS-equipped vehicles are included in the charts. There may be cases where more than one report is submitted for a crash, resulting in duplicate counts if sufficient information is not available to match the reports to the same crash. 
 
## Data Source
National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. "Standing General Order on Crash Reporting". Nhtsa.gov. Accessed June 16, 2022. https://www.nhtsa.gov/laws-regulations/standing-general-order-crash-reporting

tables.name: level_2_adas_incident_report
tables.description:
# Level 2 ADAS Incident Report Data
This table contains the observations from reported crashes of Level 2 ADAS-equipped vehicles.

## Usage Notes
From the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. Level 2 ADAS crashes are recorded 

> when the reporting entity responds "No to the ADS Equipped? field in the incident report. Reports where the latest ADS Equipped? field is blank or contains Unknown, see Narrative or Yes have not been included in these charts. There may be cases where more than one report is submitted for a crash, resulting in duplicate counts if sufficient information is not available to match the reports to the same crash.

 
## Data Source
National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. "Standing General Order on Crash Reporting". Nhtsa.gov. Accessed June 16, 2022. https://www.nhtsa.gov/laws-regulations/standing-general-order-crash-reporting

tables.name: other_incident_report_data
tables.description:
# Other Incident Report Data
This repository shows the other incident report not falling under ADS or Level 2 ADAS.

## Usage Notes
From the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. Entities subject to the General Order manufacture or operate
> different types of vehicles with different capabilities in various locations. The number of vehicles an entity has on the road, its access to crash data, operating location and many other factors could all impact a comparison.
 
## Data Source
National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, US Department of Transportation. "Standing General Order on Crash Reporting". Nhtsa.gov. Accessed June 16, 2022. https://www.nhtsa.gov/laws-regulations/standing-general-order-crash-reporting
